Chester Williams is best remembered for his part in the Boks squad which won the 1995 Rugby World Cup in South Africa. Editor's note: This livestream has ended. You may watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - Scores of people have gathered at the Newlands Rugby Stadium in Cape Town to bid farewell to late Springboks winger Chester Williams. Williams is best remembered for his part in the Boks squad which won the 1995 Rugby World Cup in South Africa. WATCH: Memorial service for the late Chester Williams He played 27 tests for South Africa, scoring 14 tries. Williams died last Friday from a heart attack. He was 49.